TableContextTimeStampBeforeTable: {493=Specially in the first years it was a huge show, with great stars like Michael Jordan or big surprises like Spud Webb. While years passed, there was less imagination, and the big stars didn't want to participate because of the risk of injuries. These were some reasons of the elimination of the Slam Dunk contest in 1998., 102=But now, since 2000, with a new generation of dunkers led by Vince Carter the show is back.}
